args:
After their clash with the Empire, Chelsea and
Mym are confronted by Menoetius during a
break in the date action. Before flying away,
he poses a curious question to them both:
＂Is love not simply another word for control?＂
In this world, strength is all. The weak\nare refuse undeserving of existence.
And humanity stands chief among them.\nYet, they have affected him. Changed him.
Clearly, someone needs to teach him the\nharsh truth; to show him how fragile, ugly,\nand base his deviant beliefs are.
EVERYBODY who gets in the way of my\ndate with Luccy gets DELETED! Aaah ha ha!
No quarter for those who stand\nin path of love! Graaaaagh!
Hot! Hot hot hot hot hot!\nFall back! Withdraw! RETREAAAT!
Well then. Looks like we didn't actually\nhave to help with that at all.
Is it weird that I kinda feel bad\nfor the imperials?
Luccy! We finished dumpstering\nall those nasty date-crashers!
I'm ready to be showered with praise,\nmy darling! Go on! Shower me!
A most impressive display, young ladies!\nThank you for driving those imperial pigs\nback from our door.
Did you come here for Valentine's?
I run a cosmetics shop here in town,\nand I'd love to repay you with a full\nmakeover, if you're interested.
I'd hate to think your look was ruined\ndefending us on such a special day.
Well, I could probably do with a bit of\nfreshening up after all that violence.
Me too! Luccy, you don't mind waiting here\nfor just an eensy, weensy minute, do you?
We'll be back more stunning than ever!
Tee hee hee! I'm even cuter now!
This little interlude is going to have my\ndarling falling for me all over again.
Luccy won't be able to look away\nfrom my adorable little face!
Your lips are ruby apples, my love...\nSo sweet... So plump...
Luuuccy! You're making me blush!\nWe couldn't POSSIBLY kiss out here in\nfront of everybody! Teeeee hee hee hee!
You appear to be enjoying yourselves.
Menoetius. And you are the Flamewyrm.
And just how do you know that?
Oh, you're rather infamous.\nBoth for your strength...
...And for your bizarre, lovestruck\ninfatuation with a human prince.
...Are you just here to mock me?
Never! Quite the opposite, in fact.\nI came only to beg a lesson.
A query to you—to both of you:\nWhat is love?
What? ...Er, well, love is the urge to\ncherish someone other than yourself.
Oh yeah, I would do anything for Luccy.\n...ANYTHING.
To cherish someone other than yourself...\nI wonder, is that really true?
Does your so-called love truly exist for the\nsake of your partner? Or is it a reflection\nof your desire to bend them to your will?
I'm busy, friend. Get to the point.

Is love not simply another word for
control? The drive to shape another in
the image of your desire, done merely
for your own self-gratification?
Of course not! Love isn't something you\nforce on someone!
Oh? Are you truly so certain your partner\nis not burdened under your affections?
Enough! Our love is no bid for control!
Then prove me wrong!\nTeach me the truth of it!
I eagerly await your answer, ladies.
Hey, wait! ...Ugh. What was THAT about?
Not only did he talk in circles,\nhe kept our dates waiting!
Yeah, you're right. Luccy's waiting.\nWe should really...hurry back...
Ah, that one seems useful indeed.\nMost excellent.
